{"cursor":"7222","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\nA 'chevron' (also spelled 'cheveron', especially in older documents) is an\ninverted V-shaped pattern. The word is usually used in reference to a kind of\nfret in architecture, or to a badge or insignia used in military or police\nuniforms to indicate rank or length of service, or in heraldry and the designs\nof flags (see flag terminology). The symbol is also used on highway signs to\nguide drivers around curves.\n","linknr":250,"url":"Chevron_(insignia)","recorded":1362677625,"links":38,"instances":["district","district","canton","district","rank","canton","district","district","heraldry","district"],"pdf":[],"categories":["Heraldic ordinaries","Ornaments","Military heraldry","Architectural elements"],"headings":["Ancient history","Heraldry","Rank insignia","Other uses as insignia","See also","References"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/5d/Chevron_demo.svg/150px-Chevron_demo.svg.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf9/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c1/Trans-coat_of_arms.svg/95px-Trans-coat_of_arms.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/72/Bioley-Magnoux-coat_of_arms.svg/95px-Bioley-Magnoux-coat_of_arms.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/5a/Flag_of_NAVA.svg/120px-Flag_of_NAVA.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f8/Bolligen-coat_of_arms.svg/95px-Bolligen-coat_of_arms.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/21/Vaumarcus-blason.png/95px-Vaumarcus-blason.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/40/Echandens-coat_of_arms.svg/95px-Echandens-coat_of_arms.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/5c/Avry-coat_of_arms.svg/95px-Avry-coat_of_arms.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/91/Army-USA-OR-02.svg/120px-Army-USA-OR-02.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a